Doc Del,<br><br>
Gald to see you back on line, old man! I missed your words of wisdom. You continue to be the best CyberDoc anywhere! <br><br>
You are entirely correct in your observation that POV wants civility and dignity on this site. They are also realistic, and fully realize that sometimes debate gets heated, but that is OK too. Even swapping mild insults and gross language has been historically tolerated.<br><br>
When the discourse becomes foul, very offensive, threatening, and consequently counterproductive to the site, then they get pissed off. I do not blame them. No one can. It is even no longer important as to who cast the first stone. The site suffers, as do those who wish to be here to learn and heal, and discuss things in a civil manner.<br><br>
There are several options that I have suggested and on the table with POV to diminish the possibility of thermonuclear events on the site. None of the options are as perfect as the one where no one has to do anything and everyone is civil.<br><br>
We have &quot;anonomous&quot; posters who plague the site somewhat, and I continue to be emphatic that no one take the bait these individuals are offering. They may tire, and eventually will go their own way. Again, voluntary action by everyone is far better than some of the options being considered.<br><br>
Doc, it is really good to see you here!<br><br>
Art 
